CSS Combinators:

Explains the relationships between the selectors.

There are different types of combinators:

# Descendant combinators ( ): Matches all the elements that are the descendants of the specified elements.

# Child combinators (>): Matches only the immediate children of the specified element.

# Adjacent sibling combinators(+): Matches only the immediate siblings of the specified siblings

# General siblings combinators(~) : Matches all the siblings of the specified siblings.
